===Etymology===
From {{etyl|hi|en}} {{m|hi|रुपीया|tr=rupīyā|sc=Deva}}, variant of {{m|hi|रुपया|tr=rupayā|sc=Deva}}/{{etyl|ur|en}} {{m|ur|رپيا|sc=ur-Arab|tr=rupayā}}, coined by [[w:Mughal Empire|Mughal emperor]] [[w:Sher Shah Suri|Sher Shah Suri]] (1540–45), from {{etyl|sa|en}} {{m|sa|रूप्यक||[[silver]] [[coin]]}}, from {{m|sa|रूप्य||[[wrought]] silver}}.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The common name for the [[monetary]] [[currency|currencies]] used in modern [[India]], [[Pakistan]], [[Nepal]], [[Sri Lanka]], [[Seychelles]], or [[Mauritius]].
# A silver coin, circulating in [[India]] 16th–20th centuries, weighing 170–180&nbsp;[[troy grain]]s (180&nbsp;troy grains from 1833) or one [[tola]].

